  • Method Details

    • size

      int size()
      Finds the number of Territories in the Linked-Web (a List of WebNodes).
      Returns:
      the size of the Linked-Web.

    • clear

      void clear()
      Clears all elements out of the Linked-Web (a List of WebNodes).

    • containsName

      boolean containsName​(String n)
      Sees if the board contains a WebNode with a particular name.
      Parameters:
      n - a non-null WebNode name.
      Returns:
      true n is found in the Linked-Web, false if n is not found in the List.

    • get

      WebNode get​(String n)
      Finds the WebNode that has a given name.
      Parameters:
      n - a non-null WebNode name that is in the Linked-Web (a List of WebNodes).
      Returns:
      the WebNode in the List that has the name n, returns null if n is not found in the List.

    • areNeighbors

      boolean areNeighbors​(String n, String b)
      Finds if two WebNode names are neighbors (share a border).
      Parameters:
      n - a non-null WebNode name that is in the Linked-Web (a List of WebNodes).
      b - a non-null WebNode name that is in the Linked-Web.
      Returns:
      true if the WebNode with name n is a neighbor of the WebNode with the name b.

    • add

      boolean add​(String n, List<String> nei, anyType v)
      Adds a WebNode to the Linked-Web (a List of WebNodes).
      Parameters:
      n - a non-null WebNode name that is not already in the Linked-Web.
      nei - a non-null List of WebNode names, representing the neighbors of the WebNode with the name n.
      v - a generic Object for the other information we want the WebNode to store.
      Returns:
      true if the WebNode is added correctly, false if there already exists a WebNode with that name in the Linked-Web.

    • remove

      WebNode remove​(String n)
      removes a WebNode with a particular name if there is one with that name on the board.
      Parameters:
      n - a non-null WebNode name that exists in the Linked-Web (a List of WebNodes).
      Returns:
      the WebNode that was successfully removed, returns null if there is no WebNode with that name in the Linked-Web.

    • set

      WebNode set​(String n, List<String> nei, anyType v)
      Changes a WebNode with a particular name to have a new set of neighbors and value.
      Parameters:
      n - a non-null WebNode name that is already in the Linked-Web (a List of WebNodes).
      nei - a non-null List of WebNode names, representing the neighbors of the WebNode with the name n.
      v - a generic Object for the other information we want the WebNode to store.
      Returns:
      the old WebNode if changed correctly, false if there is no WebNode with that name in the Linked-Web.

    • addNeighbors

      boolean addNeighbors​(String n, List<String> nei)
      Adds a collection of neighbors to a particular WebNode's list of neighbors.
      Parameters:
      n - a non-null WebNode name that exists in the WebNode List(board).
      nei - a non-null List of WebNode names, representing the neighbors of the WebNode with the name n.
      Returns:
      true if successful, false if they are all already in the list of neighbors.

    • toArray

      Object[] toArray()
      Finds the collection of all Territories in standard array form.
      Returns:
      a standard array of all Territories in the Linked-Web (a List of WebNodes).

    • showUnlinked

      String showUnlinked()
      Returns a String of all the Territories in the List (board) with one per-line, marking neighbors that do not have a matching WebNode name with *. In the form of: NORTH-WEST-TERRITORY, BORDERS:[ALASKA, ALBERTA, ONTARIO, GREENLAND] OWNER: NONE, NUMARMIES: 0 (value information dependent on what the generic anyType is)
      Returns:
      String of all formatted Territories in the List (board), marking non-matching neighbors with *.
